commit.message:
Fixed err msg for non-writable var with STO arith

It used to report "Nonexistent" because it wouldn't even look outside of
the current directory. That was a bad performance optimization: in these
cases, if the variable isn't found in the current directory, it's an
error anyway, and so the added cost of distinguishing between
"Nonexistent" and "Variable Not Writable" is irrelevant, while the
difference between those errors to the user can be very relevant.

Release 1.1.6

Fixed keyboard mapping bug in equation editor

The bug was a result of the alternate direct command mapping changes,
introduced in 1.1.5. These caused the alternate command mappings to be
applied while in the equation editor, and that is bad, because the
equation editor expects the primary command mappings.
